(10/10) At the retreat, @Ozery and I ripped it up on the slopes in Breckenridge. Alpha: snowboarding down moguls is difficult.

ETHDenver was a lot of fun this year. We loved seeing friends again.

Our dapp is coming soon! Follow @will3plan to stay updated! https://t.co/1iPAby7ntS

(9/10) The @MintGoldDust auction lit up the sports castle stage on the last night.

We got 2 RarePepes! One from the auction and one from the raffle. Special thanks to @LeValleyKelly and @theog__ for a great time! https://t.co/L9dOA8cxLE

(7/10) I had a fun conversation with @evmlabs over shots of chartreuse. We talked about #web3 games and engagement designs of existing web2 games. ğŸ®

I strongly believe in games as one of the "killer apps" of web3.

(6/10) I count myself lucky to have continuously met amazing people. The bufficorn lounge, that opened later in the week, was a great place for stimulating conversations. @NFTMerchant @Garrett_DeFi @ChazSchmidt  @katy_kin @imrane @ginge_eth @AJEhrenberg_ @patonchain @DillonLong3

(5/10) The registration line that we'd gone through in about 15 minutes less than a week earlier ballooned to a multi-hour standfest. â³

Sidenote - If you stood next to GOATs like @prodjkc, @pbrody, @AlexanderFisher in that line, you probably got to learn some amazing things.

(4/10) Tuesday of the next week was when it really got started.

More friends came into Denver, and so did a lot of new faces. I noticed that the main areas of the conference got much more congested.

(3/10) There were great talks at the Art Hotel.

The space for ETHDenver on the 4th floor was cozy, but it was big enough for the amount of people who were there. That was going to change a few days later. ğŸ˜…
